\ul\b\fs52 Lesser Gods/Unaligned Deities\par
\par
\fs40 The Whisperer of Secrets and Shroud\fs44\par
\ulnone\fs32 Alignment: \b0 True Neutral \b\f1\'b0 \f0 Domains: \b0 Arcana, Knowledge, Trickery\b\fs36\par
\b0\tab The Whisperer of Secrets and Shroud is the patron of many who find the standard, devout worship of deities too padantic and excessive for their tastes. \fs32 Not much is known regarding the inigmatic collector of secrets, and many often debate if he is actually a god in nature or not. He is most commonly praised in secret, worshipped by most in the unconventional way of amassing and sharing secrets, for a price. Those who do openly worship his benevolence often wear thick, heavy shrouds, which leave their features hidden and obscured to prying eyes, and act as a sort of collector and dealer, receiving secrets and information from other worshippers, bother open and not, and, in return, sharing secrets with them, if the payed information is worth the price.\par
\tab The appearance of the Whisperer of Secrets and Shroud is unknown, like much about the lesser deity. Many believe those who outwardly worship him dress as they do to take on his visage, which is best described as that of an ordinary ratfolk, dressed in large, thick, dark, baggy robes, complete with a hood which hangs and shrouds his face from view. Due to this, it is said that he walks among his followers, and that any one of them that you meet could be the real god, or just another devotee.\par
\tab The Whisperer of Secrets and Shrouds isn't viewed as a god, but instead as the leader of a cult in most countries, and as such he isn't given a proper temple or holy day. In many places his acolytes are forced to hide in the shadows and congregate in dark areas hidden away from the beaten path, like the sewers, as any visable, public worship of him is met with scorn and disapproval.\par
\ul\b\fs36 Commandments of the Whisperer of Secrets and Shroud\'f8\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ulnone\b0\fs28 Seek knowledge in all things. That which is most guarded has the most value.\ul\b\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\ulnone\b0 Collect secrets wherever they are. Information is often worth far more than gold.\ul\b\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\ulnone\b0 When entering new lands, seek out other followers and congregate, for secrets always flow where shrouds gather.\f1\fs22\lang9\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par
\ul\b\f0\fs40\lang1033 The Fox Spirit of Purity\fs44\par
\ulnone\fs32 Alignment: \b0 True Neutral \b\f1\'b0 \f0 Domains: \b0 Arcana, Forge, Nature\b\fs36\par
\b0\tab\fs32 Once one of the most predominantly worshipped and praised gods,  the Fox Spirit of Purity was seen as the patron goddess to farmers, warriors, and blacksmiths everywhere, but none worshipped and sung her praises more than the Kitsune, a race who's history is filled and even shapped by the goddess, whom they believed created them in her own image. Though her influence has waned greatly since the genocidal purge of the Kitsune some hundred years ago, the Fox Spirit of Purity is still worshipped within small groups and villages around the western continent of Vesper, primarily within, and around, the secluded, hidden kitsune villages.\par
\tab While she's primarily seen as a neutral deity, with her primary domain being that of purity and balance, which is usually translated better by warriors of light and good, which champion her cause, translating it to be one of forgiveness, redemption, and purification, seeking out beings that have been corrupted and tainted by various sources, such as necromancers and the undead, bringing their souls back to the way of the light, or laying them to rest when necessary. This is however, at times, seen as taking her ideals too far, as balance cannot exist with strictly good or evil. Some smiths and crafters in villages that know of, and have relations with the kitsune also worship her, believing her blessing of purity helps their craft, enabling them to refine metals, gems, and other materials to a nearly divine level, far surpassing that of any other crafter. Her most devout followers, however, are unsurprisingly the zenko, a small subrace of primarily female kitsune, believed to have been blessed by her divinity in the womb, and thus born with a very close connection to the goddess herself. The females almost always become clerics in her service, often moving up into influential roles, groomed to be natural leaders from birth, while the few male zenko turn to the innate sorcery she bestows them, or crusading her cause across the land as a paladin in her holy service.\par
\tab The Fox Spirit of Purity once had many depictions, but in her waning influence of recent years, only one predominant visage of her divinity remained: the form which was worshipped as the mother of magical foxes. Always depicted as appearing in moonlight, never during the day, the Fox Spirit of Purity takes the form of a young, beautiful, twelve-tailed kitsune woman, with both human and vulpine features. Her hair and fur are a very light, pale gold, and her skin is equally pale, almost glowing, as she wears a long, folded dress, called a kimono, often dark colored with small, white flecks printed on the fabric, like rice. Her symbol is that of a small fox shadow, covering over the full moon.\f1\par
\tab\f0 Not many outside of kitsune society know of the Fox Spirit of Purity's holy day, the Purge, which is held on the first night of each new year. The Purge, despite how violent the name sounds, is actually a very somber, mellow, and peaceful celebration. The evening is first met with a bountiful feast, where a variety of food, harvested and hunted from the nearby lands, is accompanied by sweet, fresh wines and meads, brewed from the natural honey and fruits cultivated by the kitsune, is distilled with a thin malt made from fermented rice. They spend the night feasting and being merry as a community, and the few outsiders who have witnessed the holiday celebration say the custom of repenting sins and corruption of the year's past is surprisingly met with an air of openness, acceptance, and forgiveness from the community, especially by those that have been aggrieved.\par
\ul\b\fs36 Commandments of the Fox Spirit of Purity               \'f8\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ulnone\b0\fs28 Strive for purity and balance in all things. The light cannot exist without the dark, and the dark cannot exist without the light.\ul\b\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\ulnone\b0 Waste not, want not. Do not be consumed by material greed, yet do not be afraid to seek what you covet.\ul\b\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\ulnone\b0 Peace and neutrality. There is a time for action, and there is a time for inaction; strive for the wisdom to know when is the time for both.\f1\fs22\lang9\par

